OL,6,FThe latest monthly bulletins for the
OL,7,Fprison population in England and Wales
OL,8,Falso appear to track a falling number
OL,9,Fof inmates and a decreased capacity at
OL,10,FDartmoor.
OL,12,FJanuary figures record an operational
OL,13,Fcapacity of 583, with a population of
OL,14,F555, while in February the capacity
OL,15,Fwas 505 with a population of 470.
OL,17,FIn December, a report by Dartmoor's
OL,18,Findependent monitoring board warned
OL,19,Fthe prison was understaffed and
OL,20,Fovercrowded, and arguably "not fit for
OL,21,Fpurpose".
